<p>Control the rotation of elements using the <code>.rotate-*</code>
classes. Useful for rotating icons, buttons, and other UI elements.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>.rotate-[angle]</code></pre>
<p>Optional variants:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>hover:rotate-[angle]</code>: Applies the rotation on
hover.</li>
<li><code>transition-rotate</code>: Enables smooth rotation
transitions.</li>
<li><code>duration-[time]</code>: Defines transition duration.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="doc-examples">Examples</h3>
<div class="w-fit p-3 border rounded mt-5 mb-3 rotate-180">
Upside down
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;rotate-180&quot;&gt;Upside down&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div class="w-fit p-3 border mt-5 mb-3 rounded hover:rotate-90">
Hover me
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;rotate-90&quot;&gt;Hover me&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<p>This rotates the icon by 90° when hovered, with a smooth 300ms
transition.</p>
